WEBVTT

00:00.292 --> 00:02.753
[cheering]

00:06.924 --> 00:08.926
♪ ♪

00:08.926 --> 00:11.429
[Heather] Every player
has a story.

00:21.439 --> 00:23.566
[gasps, panting]

00:25.276 --> 00:27.737
Some of them are even true.

00:32.283 --> 00:35.911
Every player is hiding
something.

00:35.911 --> 00:38.330
Secret selves...

00:40.583 --> 00:41.792
...secret habits.

00:44.837 --> 00:46.464
[phone ringing]

00:46.464 --> 00:48.591
- Secret shame.
- Hello?

00:48.591 --> 00:50.009
[operator] You have
received a collect call

00:50.009 --> 00:52.303
from an inmate
at Sayverville Unit.

00:52.303 --> 00:54.513
- Do you accept the charges?
- Yeah, go ahead. I accept.

00:57.725 --> 00:59.560
Hey, Pops.

00:59.560 --> 01:01.812
[Heather] We're all afraid
of something.

01:02.980 --> 01:04.899
[exhales]

01:06.609 --> 01:09.904
But they're never the things
we say out loud.

01:11.655 --> 01:13.824
- [Lorne] Miss Nill?
- Shit.

01:13.824 --> 01:15.826
Can you braid my hair?

01:15.826 --> 01:16.911
[Heather] Later. Lorne's here.
We got to go, okay?

01:16.911 --> 01:18.162
[Lorne] I know you're in there.

01:18.162 --> 01:20.414
- Open up.
- [Lily] Wait, my library books.

01:20.414 --> 01:23.125
[Lorne] Rent's due.

01:25.544 --> 01:27.421
Go, go.

01:27.421 --> 01:28.631
- Miss Nill?
- [stammers]

01:28.631 --> 01:30.466
Okay, come on, come on.

01:31.509 --> 01:33.219
As long as you keep moving,

01:33.219 --> 01:35.888
your fear always stays
behind you.

01:43.312 --> 01:45.314
[tires screeching]

01:49.568 --> 01:51.695
[exhales]

01:51.695 --> 01:53.781
Rent's due again, huh?

01:58.327 --> 02:01.914
[Heather] Okay, Bug. I will
see you here back at 4:00.

02:01.914 --> 02:03.541
But Bo is gonna pick us up
after his shift.

02:03.541 --> 02:05.125
Bye.

02:05.125 --> 02:08.087
So, Bo and your mom
are back together again?

02:08.087 --> 02:09.964
[Heather] Oh, yeah.
This week they are.

02:09.964 --> 02:12.007
After I make some copies
of my résumé,

02:12.007 --> 02:13.676
do you think you can drop me
off at Link's?

02:13.676 --> 02:15.636
I heard that
they might be hiring.

02:15.636 --> 02:17.680
Yeah, what's the point
of even looking for a job

02:17.680 --> 02:19.306
if you're just gonna
play the game?

02:19.306 --> 02:22.685
'Cause I have $17.26
in my savings account.

02:22.685 --> 02:24.687
Ooh. [chuckles]

02:24.687 --> 02:26.856
[beeping]

02:26.856 --> 02:29.608
Have you, um,
talked to Nat at all?

02:29.608 --> 02:31.443
She hasn't really answered
any of my calls.

02:31.443 --> 02:33.320
It's been two days.

02:33.320 --> 02:36.115
Look, it's Nat, okay?

02:36.115 --> 02:38.200
I mean, you know how she gets.

02:38.200 --> 02:39.618
This will all blow over.

02:39.618 --> 02:41.579
I didn't mean to lie.

02:41.579 --> 02:43.163
I didn't even
really mean to jump.

02:43.163 --> 02:45.165
You know?

02:45.165 --> 02:48.085
But when I was up there,
it was like I had to do it.

02:48.085 --> 02:51.463
- But you don't.
- You think I should quit?

02:51.463 --> 02:53.549
Yeah, I mean,
players do it all the time.

02:53.549 --> 02:54.758
No.

02:56.427 --> 02:59.054
Look, Panic is bullshit,
Heather.

02:59.054 --> 03:01.390
It's-it's bullshit,
and it's-it's dangerous,

03:01.390 --> 03:03.309
a-and two kids died last year,
so-so what's the point?

03:03.309 --> 03:05.060
I mean, you know you can't win.

03:05.060 --> 03:07.062
- You know you're just
gonna be sidelined.
- Is that what you think?

03:07.062 --> 03:08.731
[stammers softly]

03:08.731 --> 03:10.941
You think I can't win?

03:10.941 --> 03:12.526
No, I-I...

03:12.526 --> 03:14.111
I bet that's what
everyone thinks.

03:18.198 --> 03:20.826
[Cortez] So, graduation is over

03:20.826 --> 03:23.329
and summertime has begun,
and unfortunately,

03:23.329 --> 03:26.081
so has this game
the kids call Panic.

03:26.081 --> 03:29.376
Supposedly, Jimmy and Abby
were playing this game.

03:29.376 --> 03:33.714
17 years old, young and in love,
headed to college.

03:34.757 --> 03:36.091
And now they're dead.

03:39.136 --> 03:42.765
As you know, Abby was run over
by an 18-wheeler.

03:42.765 --> 03:45.726
She tried to cross
I-45 blindfolded.

03:47.853 --> 03:49.021
[horn honking]

03:54.443 --> 03:55.653
And Jimmy...

03:57.738 --> 03:59.740
Jimmy killed himself

03:59.740 --> 04:01.742
playing a game
of Russian roulette.

04:01.742 --> 04:03.744
♪ ♪

04:12.044 --> 04:13.837
[gunshot]

04:14.838 --> 04:17.549
Now, one thing is clear:
this game is organized.

04:17.549 --> 04:19.468
Whoever lit up
those fireworks, well,

04:19.468 --> 04:21.679
they wanted to send us
on a wild-goose chase.

04:21.679 --> 04:23.013
Yeah, it worked pretty good.

04:23.013 --> 04:24.890
- Yeah, it did.
- [Langley] Sir?

04:24.890 --> 04:27.726
I talked to dispatch about
the complaint calls that night,

04:27.726 --> 04:30.062
and one of the callers
was Myra Campbell.

04:30.062 --> 04:32.022
I know Myra Campbell.
She was Abby's best friend.

04:32.022 --> 04:33.941
[Langley] Well, we talked
to her over the winter,

04:33.941 --> 04:35.651
and she said
she didn't know anything then.

04:35.651 --> 04:38.529
But... she sounded really upset
on those calls.

04:38.529 --> 04:41.532
Well, maybe those fireworks
jogged her memory.

04:42.825 --> 04:44.034
Let's talk to her again.

04:44.034 --> 04:45.327
Okay.

04:45.327 --> 04:47.746
These kids follow the herd.

04:47.746 --> 04:49.498
They protect themselves,
they protect this thing,

04:49.498 --> 04:50.624
and that's it.

04:52.418 --> 04:55.170
Last year, this town put
two of our kids in the ground.

04:56.422 --> 04:58.424
And someone's gonna pay.

05:14.148 --> 05:15.607
Hey, Mindy.

05:15.607 --> 05:17.609
Hey, Heather.

05:19.028 --> 05:21.321
Do you guys have
any jobs available?

05:21.321 --> 05:23.699
We are all full up
for the summer.

05:23.699 --> 05:26.035
You try over at the Buc-ee's?

05:26.035 --> 05:28.829
Yeah, I've tried everywhere.

05:28.829 --> 05:30.706
[Mindy] Well, you can
leave a résumé

05:30.706 --> 05:32.624
in case something opens up.

05:32.624 --> 05:33.876
Thank you.

05:33.876 --> 05:35.252
- [keys drop]
- [woman grunts]

05:38.130 --> 05:39.715
Hey, I got-- I got you!

05:39.715 --> 05:40.883
Wow!

05:40.883 --> 05:42.676
Thank you.

05:42.676 --> 05:44.803
Almost lost a man
overboard there.

05:44.803 --> 05:47.139
- [dog barks]
- Oh, Rigley!

05:47.139 --> 05:49.224
- Oh, hey, hey...
- Rigley, get back here!

05:49.224 --> 05:52.561
Get back here now!
What are you doing?

05:52.561 --> 05:54.354
- [Heather] Good boy.
- My escape artist.

05:54.354 --> 05:55.731
[laughs]

05:55.731 --> 05:57.816
Bad, Rigley.

05:57.816 --> 06:00.069
Oh, hi. [chuckles]

06:00.069 --> 06:02.029
[Rigley barks]

06:02.029 --> 06:04.323
He's usually not that friendly
with strangers.

06:04.323 --> 06:05.866
You're a dog person.

06:05.866 --> 06:08.911
No, I mean, not really,
I just...

06:08.911 --> 06:12.289
My mom always told us that
if it can't pee in a toilet,

06:12.289 --> 06:14.458
then it shouldn't live
in a house.

06:14.458 --> 06:17.127
At least dogs never
leave the seat up.

06:17.127 --> 06:19.088
Plus they do
what you tell them to.

06:19.088 --> 06:20.547
Most of the time.

06:20.547 --> 06:21.632
Rigley, up.

06:21.632 --> 06:23.759
Good dog!

06:23.759 --> 06:26.845
Got this.

06:26.845 --> 06:28.847
That one.

06:32.101 --> 06:34.686
I'm Anne, by the way.

06:34.686 --> 06:36.438
Heather.

06:36.438 --> 06:37.689
- Heather?
- Mm-hmm.

06:37.689 --> 06:39.817
I heard you asking
after a job in there?

06:39.817 --> 06:43.153
- Yeah.
- 'Cause I could use
some help out at my farm.

06:43.153 --> 06:46.240
Nothing fancy-- I got a couple
of sheds that need painting.

06:46.240 --> 06:48.700
It's not glamorous,
but I pay cash.

06:48.700 --> 06:50.661
- Interested?
- Are you serious?

06:50.661 --> 06:52.663
Certainly hope so.

06:52.663 --> 06:56.208
You know the, uh, farm
at the end of Old River Road?

06:56.208 --> 06:58.836
- Yeah.
- That's my place.

06:58.836 --> 07:01.755
Mornings are best.

07:05.509 --> 07:07.928
Hey, why me?

07:09.304 --> 07:11.306
Why not you?

07:12.683 --> 07:14.726
- [door closes]
- [engine starts]

07:20.983 --> 07:23.694
[phone beeps]

07:34.913 --> 07:36.915
She's still your best friend.

07:41.670 --> 07:43.422
All right, remember
the court rules: no cursing,

07:43.422 --> 07:45.174
spitting, hitting or crying,

07:45.174 --> 07:46.717
because I think I ran
out of tissues.

07:48.969 --> 07:50.679
Can you just...?

07:50.679 --> 07:52.264
Can you just give us a second?

07:52.264 --> 07:54.266
Yeah, yeah, h-happily, yeah.

07:58.020 --> 07:59.396
Can we go talk over there?

07:59.396 --> 08:01.148
Fine.

08:09.865 --> 08:11.450
So?

08:11.450 --> 08:15.245
My mom took my money for school.

08:15.245 --> 08:17.289
What do you mean she took it?

08:17.289 --> 08:20.125
Her car needed
a new transmission.

08:20.125 --> 08:22.085
Guess she thought I owed it
to her for freeloading,

08:22.085 --> 08:24.713
like, toilet paper
and food and stuff.

08:24.713 --> 08:26.632
How much?

08:26.632 --> 08:29.218
$5,460.

08:30.594 --> 08:32.596
She left a few bucks
in spare change, though.

08:34.932 --> 08:37.643
I wish you'd told me.

08:37.643 --> 08:39.937
I didn't really have
a chance to.

08:39.937 --> 08:41.355
I didn't learn about it
till after

08:41.355 --> 08:42.898
you had left for the Jump and...

08:44.274 --> 08:46.902
...when I found out,
it was like I couldn't...

08:46.902 --> 08:48.904
even think.

08:49.905 --> 08:51.490
It was like I had a hand
around my throat.

08:51.490 --> 08:53.492
It was like I couldn't
even talk about it.

08:57.871 --> 09:00.332
I'm sorry, Nat.

09:00.332 --> 09:03.001
I never meant to compete
against you.

09:03.001 --> 09:05.379
I know.

09:05.379 --> 09:07.422
I'm sorry for getting so mad.

09:07.422 --> 09:10.425
I should've known
you'd have a reason.

09:12.970 --> 09:15.639
What I want to know is...

09:17.808 --> 09:20.852
...how are we gonna
win this thing?

09:20.852 --> 09:22.604
- What do you mean?
- Oh.

09:22.604 --> 09:24.523
If we're both in the game,
we're in it together.

09:24.523 --> 09:26.400
I thought you said there was
no together in Panic.

09:26.400 --> 09:28.277
Uh, there's no ties.

09:28.277 --> 09:30.362
One winner only, but...

09:30.362 --> 09:31.780
if we work together,

09:31.780 --> 09:33.824
then the both of us win
if either of us do.

09:35.450 --> 09:36.702
And then we split the money.

09:38.036 --> 09:40.872
Oh, I will take that as a yes.

09:40.872 --> 09:42.791
[door opens]

09:42.791 --> 09:45.419
Are you guys gonna make out?

09:45.419 --> 09:47.170
- You wish.
- Really?

09:47.170 --> 09:48.547
So, all good?

09:48.547 --> 09:50.549
You guys friends again?

09:52.384 --> 09:54.845
Partners.

10:08.358 --> 10:09.776
[Myra] Who is it?

10:09.776 --> 10:11.361
Sergeant Langley,
Sheriff's Department.

10:20.162 --> 10:22.539
Hi. Myra Campbell?

10:22.539 --> 10:25.375
Sergeant Langley.
You mind if I come in?

10:27.669 --> 10:29.671
[dog barking in distance]

10:29.671 --> 10:31.673
It was my day off.

10:31.673 --> 10:33.050
Oh, yeah?

10:36.511 --> 10:38.847
What kind of work do you do?

10:38.847 --> 10:41.933
[sighs] Assistant manager
of a Taco Bell.

10:41.933 --> 10:43.769
I work up at the airport.

10:43.769 --> 10:47.814
[Langley] You always stay home
and drink on your day off?

10:47.814 --> 10:50.150
Sometimes I drink
somewhere else.

10:53.070 --> 10:55.739
But you didn't come here
to talk about me, did you?

10:55.739 --> 10:59.034
No. I came here
to talk to you about Panic.

10:59.034 --> 11:01.328
I told your friends
back in March

11:01.328 --> 11:03.330
I had nothing to say.

11:03.330 --> 11:05.374
I never played.

11:05.374 --> 11:07.376
Abby Clark did, though.

11:07.376 --> 11:09.503
She was your best friend,
wasn't she?

11:09.503 --> 11:12.672
I'm sure she told you
some secrets.

11:12.672 --> 11:15.342
Some of them.

11:15.342 --> 11:17.594
And I swore I'd never tell.

11:17.594 --> 11:19.679
I gotcha.

11:19.679 --> 11:21.681
I don't know,
I just thought after that earful

11:21.681 --> 11:23.558
you gave dispatch last week
about those fireworks

11:23.558 --> 11:26.186
- going off, maybe...
- You know the real problem
with this town?

11:26.186 --> 11:28.438
It's not Panic.

11:28.438 --> 11:30.565
It's not the players...

11:30.565 --> 11:31.942
or the judges.

11:31.942 --> 11:35.237
- At least they're trying.
- The judges?

11:40.575 --> 11:42.953
Are the judges the ones
that plan the game?

11:43.995 --> 11:46.248
Maybe.

11:46.248 --> 11:51.044
- "Maybe."
- I told you, I didn't play.

11:51.044 --> 11:53.004
All I know...

11:53.004 --> 11:55.924
is what I've heard.

11:55.924 --> 11:59.261
- Okay?
- Okay.

11:59.261 --> 12:02.681
Okay. Well, uh,
if you hear anything else,

12:02.681 --> 12:04.599
do you mind
just giving me a call?

12:04.599 --> 12:06.601
I'd appreciate it.

12:08.186 --> 12:10.188
Thank you, Myra.

12:11.523 --> 12:13.733
Sergeant Langley?

12:13.733 --> 12:15.444
You didn't let me finish.

12:15.444 --> 12:16.945
Be careful.

12:16.945 --> 12:19.281
The game will go on.

12:19.281 --> 12:21.533
The signs are everywhere.

12:28.039 --> 12:30.041
♪ ♪

12:34.129 --> 12:37.591
Hey. Keep your eyes
where they belong.

12:37.591 --> 12:39.426
[Natalie] Please.
They are, trust me.

12:41.470 --> 12:44.181
And what kind of person doesn't
have a social media account?

12:44.181 --> 12:45.640
A sane one.

12:45.640 --> 12:47.434
- [Bishop] Careful.
- Hey, do you think

12:47.434 --> 12:49.394
now that the judges
know who we are,

12:49.394 --> 12:51.062
that they're watching us?

12:51.062 --> 12:52.856
Of course they're watching.

12:52.856 --> 12:55.984
How else are they gonna get
intel on all the players?

12:55.984 --> 12:59.571
They're probably
tracking where we work...

12:59.571 --> 13:01.031
[preacher] ...deception
of the tireless Antichrist.

13:01.031 --> 13:02.657
[Natalie] ...and live...

13:02.657 --> 13:04.367
[preacher] Do not deviate
from the path...

13:04.367 --> 13:06.328
I'm going to work.

13:06.328 --> 13:07.996
[preacher] ...will still find
yourself seated with the rest

13:07.996 --> 13:10.248
of the heathens,
next to the Devil.

13:10.248 --> 13:13.251
[Natalie] ...and hang out...

13:13.251 --> 13:16.254
watching what we do when we
think there's no one watching,

13:16.254 --> 13:18.423
keeping tabs on who we're with.

13:18.423 --> 13:19.716
We're squared up.

13:19.716 --> 13:21.927
They're studying
all the players.

13:28.266 --> 13:30.143
What, no invitation?

13:30.143 --> 13:31.686
Nope.

13:36.191 --> 13:39.569
Uh, we were actually
just leaving.

13:39.569 --> 13:40.904
- Hmm.
- Mm.

13:40.904 --> 13:42.030
Mm.

13:43.240 --> 13:45.283
I'm just saying hello
to the new kid.

13:46.535 --> 13:47.702
Cool.

13:49.579 --> 13:51.414
Let's get out of here.

13:52.415 --> 13:54.292
Thanks.

14:02.259 --> 14:04.261
Can I help you with something?

14:04.261 --> 14:06.263
- Yeah.
- [clears throat]

14:06.263 --> 14:07.889
Go ahead and give me

14:07.889 --> 14:09.683
the... fuck you.

14:09.683 --> 14:11.893
I'm here to help you.

14:11.893 --> 14:15.021
Look... I know you're
the new guy in town,

14:15.021 --> 14:17.440
and you probably heard about
the game, and you probably heard

14:17.440 --> 14:19.651
- it was one big
fuckin' hard-on...
- Get to the point?

14:19.651 --> 14:21.236
The point is,

14:21.236 --> 14:23.071
Panic's a local game.

14:23.071 --> 14:25.073
We made it. We run it.

14:25.073 --> 14:27.075
We keep it a secret.

14:27.075 --> 14:29.077
Strangers aren't welcome.

14:29.077 --> 14:30.579
All graduating seniors

14:30.579 --> 14:32.539
are eligible
to play the game, right?

14:32.539 --> 14:35.250
And very few
are eligible to win.

14:35.250 --> 14:38.878
I was pretty eligible when I got
those 25 points from the Jump.

14:38.878 --> 14:41.006
[laughing]

14:41.006 --> 14:42.465
I like you.

14:42.465 --> 14:43.883
I like you, I do.

14:43.883 --> 14:46.595
I like a man ain't afraid
to get his ass beat.

14:46.595 --> 14:48.096
It's gonna make it
all that much sweeter

14:48.096 --> 14:50.473
- when I beat his ass.
- [slaps counter]

14:52.267 --> 14:54.019
[door bells jingle]

14:54.019 --> 14:56.021
So, Diggins really hasn't said
when the next challenge

14:56.021 --> 14:57.814
- is gonna be yet?
- Don't look at me.

14:57.814 --> 14:59.566
I'm not trying to be
an accomplice.

14:59.566 --> 15:01.067
Uh, guys?

15:01.067 --> 15:02.527
What's that?

15:02.527 --> 15:04.029
[Bishop] Typical.

15:04.029 --> 15:06.114
Only a couple days
after graduation,

15:06.114 --> 15:09.034
and already half the letters
have dipped out.

15:11.578 --> 15:13.788
[Heather] Hey, it's a clue.

15:15.874 --> 15:18.043
Look, the missing letters
spell something.

15:18.043 --> 15:21.546
G-R-A-N-A-R-Y.

15:21.546 --> 15:23.506
Granary.

15:23.506 --> 15:27.218
So we know where
the next challenge will be.

15:27.218 --> 15:29.596
- The question is...
- When?

15:30.972 --> 15:33.099
So it looks like we're looking
for a start time.

15:33.099 --> 15:36.978
Maybe we'll find it
at the granary.

15:36.978 --> 15:39.105
[Bishop] I'm kind of surprised
you actually came up here.

15:39.105 --> 15:41.191
[Heather] We couldn't all spend
all of seventh grade

15:41.191 --> 15:43.693
climbing up here to scan the sky
for alien radio signals.

15:43.693 --> 15:45.737
[Bishop] No, it was
all of sixth grade.

15:45.737 --> 15:48.740
In seventh grade,
I came up here to look at porn.

15:48.740 --> 15:50.408
- [Heather] How romantic.
- Nah, nah. Tonight...

15:50.408 --> 15:52.911
tonight is about you.

15:52.911 --> 15:56.790
Think of it as a...
training exercise.

15:56.790 --> 15:58.333
Well, I highly doubt

15:58.333 --> 16:00.960
the challenge
will involve snack food.

16:00.960 --> 16:02.420
All right, enough chitchat.

16:02.420 --> 16:04.297
We're supposed
to be looking for clues.

16:04.297 --> 16:05.715
[Bishop] You see anything?

16:06.758 --> 16:09.177
I don't know, let me look. Um...

16:09.177 --> 16:11.012
major structural hazard.

16:11.012 --> 16:13.223
Old chemical drums.

16:13.223 --> 16:15.058
Snake nirvana.

16:15.058 --> 16:18.978
And at least six luxury
high-rise condos for rats.

16:18.978 --> 16:21.564
- So yeah,
everything seems normal.
- Hey, how much do you think

16:21.564 --> 16:23.066
they're charging rats for rent
around here?

16:23.066 --> 16:24.859
Not funny.

16:24.859 --> 16:26.444
Not good. Not your best.

16:29.948 --> 16:32.992
Look. Heather,
what I said at the library...

16:32.992 --> 16:35.120
When I said you couldn't win,

16:35.120 --> 16:36.246
- I...
- It's okay.

16:36.246 --> 16:37.956
No, no, no. Listen.

16:39.290 --> 16:41.626
I didn't mean you
couldn't win Panic specifically,

16:41.626 --> 16:43.420
I meant generally.

16:43.420 --> 16:45.046
You can't win.

16:45.046 --> 16:47.257
I mean, sure, people
take home the grand prize,

16:47.257 --> 16:49.175
but how many people
actually win Panic?

16:49.175 --> 16:51.886
Conrad Spurlock got out.
He moved to Florida.

16:51.886 --> 16:53.430
Yeah, because he would have
otherwise been arrested.

16:53.430 --> 16:55.140
People say he was stealing cars
with Luke Hall.

16:55.140 --> 16:57.434
- I mean, they killed a girl.
- Okay, I heard that

16:57.434 --> 16:59.018
that had nothing to do
with the game.

16:59.018 --> 17:00.979
- That they stole the car...
- Exactly.

17:00.979 --> 17:03.064
Because winning Panic
didn't fix anything.

17:03.064 --> 17:05.275
It didn't save them
from making stupid choices.

17:05.275 --> 17:08.820
It only bought them chances
to make even dumber ones.

17:08.820 --> 17:10.238
[Bishop sighs]

17:10.238 --> 17:12.907
You can buy stupid choices;
you can buy smart ones.

17:12.907 --> 17:14.909
No, you don't buy 'em.

17:16.911 --> 17:19.414
You only pay for the bad ones.

17:19.414 --> 17:22.459
♪ ♪

17:25.128 --> 17:27.797
[insects chirping]

17:43.521 --> 17:45.523
♪ ♪

18:02.624 --> 18:05.126
♪ ♪

18:07.587 --> 18:09.923
[Langley] Williams,
I think I got something.

18:09.923 --> 18:12.175
Has there been
any suspicious activity

18:12.175 --> 18:14.135
at the granary lately?

18:14.135 --> 18:16.429
[Williams] Funny
you should ask, Langley.

18:16.429 --> 18:18.389
We just got a complaint
on some graffiti.

18:18.389 --> 18:20.558
Apparently it went up overnight.

18:26.272 --> 18:30.109
This is not a real number,
because it's missing two digits.

18:30.109 --> 18:32.320
I'm thinking, like,
it's a geotag, or...

18:32.320 --> 18:34.030
[Williams] Okay,
so what is this? Is this, like,

18:34.030 --> 18:35.448
a scavenger hunt?

18:35.448 --> 18:37.951
These kids are running around
looking for clues?

18:39.327 --> 18:41.204
[exhales] I don't know.

18:41.204 --> 18:43.706
I had Hernandez run
numbers and addresses

18:43.706 --> 18:46.709
for every Stan, Stanley,
Stanton, Stanson and Stanner

18:46.709 --> 18:48.211
in the county.

18:48.211 --> 18:50.839
If I were you,
I would divide and conquer.

18:54.092 --> 18:55.927
You really outdid yourself.

18:55.927 --> 18:58.346
Oh. Well, you know
what I always say:

18:58.346 --> 19:00.348
preparation beats perspiration.

19:00.348 --> 19:03.226
- You have never ever said that.
- Just sit down already.

19:03.226 --> 19:06.563
Well, if we're gonna win,
we got to do our homework.

19:06.563 --> 19:08.565
Yes, Ms. Williams.

19:08.565 --> 19:09.941
Starting with the players
we think

19:09.941 --> 19:12.402
- are most likely to win.
- Okay.

19:12.402 --> 19:13.570
[Natalie] Ray Hall.

19:13.570 --> 19:14.863
Everyone's betting on him.

19:14.863 --> 19:17.782
He's reckless, fearless.
He's not afraid of pain.

19:17.782 --> 19:20.285
- Also, he might be
a psychopath.
- Ooh, also that.

19:20.285 --> 19:21.911
And he's a legacy.
His brother Luke

19:21.911 --> 19:24.205
won the game a few years ago.

19:24.205 --> 19:26.124
[Natalie] What do we think
of Tyler Young's chances?

19:26.124 --> 19:27.876
I don't know, I mean, you're
the one who used to date him.

19:27.876 --> 19:29.252
[scoffs] I was a sophomore.

19:29.252 --> 19:30.545
Anything you do
before junior year

19:30.545 --> 19:32.046
can't be legally held
against you.

19:32.046 --> 19:34.549
Besides, eh, we hooked up,
like, four times.

19:34.549 --> 19:37.927
- Well, I have five and a half.
- I still put Young at 50/50.

19:37.927 --> 19:40.471
On the one hand, he's too dumb
to be scared of much.

19:40.471 --> 19:42.724
- On the other hand...
- That tribal tattoo is
a sign of weakness.

19:42.724 --> 19:44.851
Ugh. I was gonna say
he doesn't need the money.

19:44.851 --> 19:46.644
Ah. Pharma.

19:46.644 --> 19:48.187
It's good that Adam Lyons
is up there,

19:48.187 --> 19:49.480
'cause he's basically
just a walking appendage.

19:49.480 --> 19:50.857
Totally.

19:50.857 --> 19:53.818
- What about Troy Van?
- Mm, Troy Van.

19:53.818 --> 19:56.487
[Heather] I mean, if you can
wear lip gloss in Carp, Texas,

19:56.487 --> 19:58.156
then you've got to be
kind of a badass.

19:58.156 --> 20:01.075
Good point. I think
Shawna Kenny could be a problem.

20:01.075 --> 20:03.786
Her brother, Hunt,
is coaching her.

20:03.786 --> 20:05.330
And she's just so fucking cool.

20:05.330 --> 20:07.081
Last but not least...

20:07.081 --> 20:08.499
the new kid.

20:08.499 --> 20:11.628
Dodge Mason,
mysterious backstory.

20:11.628 --> 20:15.423
- Motivations unknown.
Weaknesses undetermined.
- So I'm guessing that'll be

20:15.423 --> 20:18.718
- just a swipe right
from you, then.
- Okay, okay.

20:18.718 --> 20:21.095
Now on to the main event.

20:21.095 --> 20:24.223
Challenges usually fall under
a couple different categories.

20:24.223 --> 20:27.268
We have labyrinths
and wilderness drops.

20:27.268 --> 20:28.853
[owl hooting]

20:29.896 --> 20:32.190
Thefts and illegal entry.

20:32.190 --> 20:33.399
[glass breaks]

20:36.444 --> 20:38.196
Ugh, all the gross stuff,

20:38.196 --> 20:39.989
like snakes, rats and spiders.

20:39.989 --> 20:41.240
Pass.

20:41.240 --> 20:43.201
Challenges of physical stamina
under pain

20:43.201 --> 20:44.661
or stress.

20:44.661 --> 20:46.329
Heights.

20:46.329 --> 20:47.956
Drop-offs.

20:47.956 --> 20:49.582
I'd bet anything tonight

20:49.582 --> 20:52.001
that the challenge
will be a crossing.

20:52.001 --> 20:54.295
The points will be for speed.

20:54.295 --> 20:56.130
Isn't that how Abby died?

20:57.757 --> 20:59.217
Easy.

20:59.217 --> 21:00.551
♪ ♪

21:00.551 --> 21:03.179
♪ I don't follow rules
from nobody ♪

21:03.179 --> 21:05.431
♪ Get up out my face,
you're nobody ♪

21:05.431 --> 21:07.058
♪ Nobody ♪

21:07.058 --> 21:09.394
♪ If I'm just a girl,
then stop running... ♪

21:09.394 --> 21:13.022
[cheering]

21:13.022 --> 21:14.816
♪ Stupid girl,
get it together... ♪

21:14.816 --> 21:16.609
[Diggins] Let me hear it
over there!

21:16.609 --> 21:18.987
Let me hear it over there!

21:18.987 --> 21:21.406
[cheering]

21:21.406 --> 21:24.993
All right, boys and girls,
chicks and dicks,

21:24.993 --> 21:26.411
Ray,

21:26.411 --> 21:29.330
welcome to challenge numero dos,

21:29.330 --> 21:31.290
Walk the Plank.

21:31.290 --> 21:33.459
[cheering]

21:33.459 --> 21:34.877
And reminder,

21:34.877 --> 21:37.171
we have 23 players
in the competition.

21:37.171 --> 21:39.507
All players receive 100 points
for joining

21:39.507 --> 21:42.635
except for Dodge Mason,
who gets an extra 25...

21:42.635 --> 21:44.345
[booing]

21:44.345 --> 21:47.181
I don't see him.
Maybe he missed the sign.

21:47.181 --> 21:49.183
- That's good news.
- ...and Heather Nill,

21:49.183 --> 21:51.436
who gets an extra 50 points
and immunity

21:51.436 --> 21:54.522
- in a challenge of her choice.
- [whoops] Heather!

21:54.522 --> 21:55.982
[cheering]

21:55.982 --> 21:57.525
He's here.

21:57.525 --> 21:59.110
- Maybe I should go say hi.
- [Heather] Hey,

21:59.110 --> 22:00.570
no fraternizing with the enemy,

22:00.570 --> 22:02.488
- okay?
- Fraternizing is how we find

22:02.488 --> 22:04.657
- the enemy's weak spots.
- [Diggins] Helping me

22:04.657 --> 22:07.618
keep records
is the ravishing Summer Calvo.

22:07.618 --> 22:09.162
[cheering]

22:09.162 --> 22:10.329
I'd hit it.

22:10.329 --> 22:12.707
Tonight,
points work by deduction.

22:12.707 --> 22:15.168
The slower you are,
more points you lose.

22:15.168 --> 22:17.920
- [timer beeps]
- You got 90 seconds to cross

22:17.920 --> 22:19.630
before you are in the red

22:19.630 --> 22:20.798
and out of the game.

22:20.798 --> 22:22.425
And now,

22:22.425 --> 22:24.844
in no particular order...

22:24.844 --> 22:27.388
Drumroll, please.

22:27.388 --> 22:30.016
[cheering]

22:33.186 --> 22:35.813
- Drew Santiago.
- Santiago.

22:35.813 --> 22:37.899
- [cheering]
- Holy shit! Whoo!

22:37.899 --> 22:39.901
Let's do this!

22:43.696 --> 22:45.573
[girl] Drew Santiago!

22:46.949 --> 22:49.160
Hey, since when
is Bishop friends

22:49.160 --> 22:50.787
- with Leela?
- [Leela chuckles]

22:50.787 --> 22:53.122
[Natalie] They probably know
each other from church.

22:53.122 --> 22:54.624
It's where people go
to socialize.

22:54.624 --> 22:56.000
And judge each other.

22:56.000 --> 22:58.294
Mm, exactly. Socialize.

23:07.303 --> 23:08.930
Don't break the plank, buddy.

23:08.930 --> 23:10.348
[laughs]

23:10.348 --> 23:11.474
Nice of you to join us.

23:11.474 --> 23:13.101
- How are you?
- Oh.

23:15.937 --> 23:18.439
[metal creaking]

23:18.439 --> 23:20.483
[grunting softly]

23:23.027 --> 23:24.278
Shit.

23:24.278 --> 23:26.030
Drew, you got this!

23:26.030 --> 23:27.240
- [boy] Go, Drew!
- [girl] Drew!

23:27.240 --> 23:31.285
Drew, your timer starts
three, two,

23:31.285 --> 23:33.621
- one.
- Go!

23:33.621 --> 23:35.623
- [cheering]
- [metal creaking]

23:40.086 --> 23:42.463
[girl] Yeah, you can do it!

23:42.463 --> 23:45.466
[scattered cheering]

23:51.180 --> 23:53.850
Holy fuck.

24:00.481 --> 24:02.400
[laughs, whoops]

24:02.400 --> 24:04.277
- [cheering]
- Fuck you, Ray!

24:04.277 --> 24:05.736
I didn't break the plank!

24:05.736 --> 24:08.281
[whooping]

24:09.323 --> 24:10.908
Big surprise.

24:10.908 --> 24:13.119
[laughs]
Big surprise.

24:13.119 --> 24:14.787
[Diggins] Next up...

24:14.787 --> 24:16.914
Looks like Shawna Kenny!

24:16.914 --> 24:20.042
- Shawna Kenny, you're up!
- [cheering]

24:20.042 --> 24:21.460
Go.

24:21.460 --> 24:24.505
Yeah! [whooping]

24:32.680 --> 24:36.100
[sniffs, sighs]

24:37.476 --> 24:40.146
- No, dude. No, no, no, no, no.
- Oh, Langley.

24:40.146 --> 24:42.732
- Here. You're welcome.
- Thank you.

24:44.025 --> 24:45.276
Are you having any luck?

24:45.276 --> 24:47.612
Ah, ruled out every kind
of Stan in the county.

24:47.612 --> 24:49.488
It's all Greek to me.

24:52.158 --> 24:53.993
What?

24:53.993 --> 24:56.537
[laughs]
Greeks and Romans.

24:56.537 --> 24:58.956
Oh, my God. Oh, my God.

24:58.956 --> 25:01.751
Yes. Okay. So, so, the Romans,
they used letters

25:01.751 --> 25:03.502
for their numerical system.
Look.

25:03.502 --> 25:05.838
What if this graffiti
is using numbers

25:05.838 --> 25:07.465
to give us a message?

25:07.465 --> 25:09.300
One, "O."

25:09.300 --> 25:11.177
Two, "D." Three... See?

25:11.177 --> 25:13.679
S-So, wait, okay. Okay.

25:13.679 --> 25:15.473
So, "O" is one.

25:15.473 --> 25:17.475
[cheering]

25:21.646 --> 25:25.441
And Ray Hall makes it across
in 17 seconds,

25:25.441 --> 25:27.318
setting the new record to beat!

25:28.986 --> 25:30.947
[whoops]

25:30.947 --> 25:32.823
Oh, yeah!

25:32.823 --> 25:35.117
- [whoops]
- [Summer] Next up,

25:35.117 --> 25:37.536
Heather Nill.

25:37.536 --> 25:39.538
[Diggins] Heather, you're up.

25:42.959 --> 25:44.543
Wish me luck.

25:44.543 --> 25:46.963
You'll do great. Just...

25:46.963 --> 25:49.090
don't look down.

25:49.090 --> 25:51.133
It's literally
the only place to look.

25:51.133 --> 25:54.053
Wait. Wait. Um...

25:54.053 --> 25:56.180
[exhales]

25:56.180 --> 25:58.683
Just... just be careful.

25:58.683 --> 26:00.518
Okay?

26:01.519 --> 26:04.063
Heather, it's, uh, now or never.

26:10.861 --> 26:12.863
♪ ♪

26:14.782 --> 26:16.784
[scattered cheering]

26:25.793 --> 26:27.211
[boy] Go, Heather!

26:41.392 --> 26:43.394
Heather,
your timer starts in three,

26:43.394 --> 26:45.855
- two, one.
- Wait, Diggins.

26:45.855 --> 26:47.231
- [Summer] Go!
- [cheering]

26:49.900 --> 26:51.902
[metal creaking]

26:53.029 --> 26:54.697
[whispers]
Shit. Sh-Sh-Shit.

26:54.697 --> 26:57.033
[Summer] Five seconds!

26:57.033 --> 26:58.784
- I can't look.
- Oh, my God.

27:04.665 --> 27:07.168
[Summer] Ten seconds!

27:07.168 --> 27:09.295
[groaning]

27:12.173 --> 27:14.383
[Natalie] Come on,
Heather, you got this!

27:14.383 --> 27:16.844
Come on. Come on.
You got it! You got it! Just go.

27:16.844 --> 27:19.847
[Summer] Twenty-three seconds!

27:21.265 --> 27:23.517
[Bishop] Come on, come on,
come on, you got it!

27:23.517 --> 27:25.728
- [Adam] Under-over on Nill?
- [Tyler] Mm.

27:25.728 --> 27:29.065
She's out, man. I've seen snails
move faster than that.

27:29.065 --> 27:30.649
- Fuck.
- [others gasping]

27:30.649 --> 27:32.568
- Fuck.
- [boy] Whoa!

27:34.945 --> 27:37.365
- Just breathe. Go.
- Uh, tell me when it's over.

27:37.365 --> 27:40.159
[Ray] Yo, Nill.
Hey, you want to sit around

27:40.159 --> 27:42.953
showing your ass all night,
they got openings at Scarlett's.

27:42.953 --> 27:44.580
Isn't that where you buy
all your girlfriends?

27:44.580 --> 27:46.290
[Ray] I get my girlfriends
all around, darling.

27:46.290 --> 27:48.042
But they sit on my lap for free.

27:48.042 --> 27:50.294
[Heather] You know,
I knew you were stupid.

27:50.294 --> 27:52.630
But what you just said
really just drove it home.

27:55.091 --> 27:57.426
That's the thing
about stupid decisions.

27:57.426 --> 27:59.553
They're always the fun ones.

27:59.553 --> 28:01.639
Don't you have
anywhere else to be?

28:01.639 --> 28:05.017
[Ray] No.
What could be better than this?

28:05.017 --> 28:06.185
What is he saying?

28:06.185 --> 28:07.645
[Natalie] Come on, Heather.

28:07.645 --> 28:10.564
[Summer] Forty-eight seconds.

28:11.774 --> 28:14.360
Get a little closer.

28:14.360 --> 28:16.278
Closer.

28:20.241 --> 28:21.992
[cheering and applause]

28:21.992 --> 28:23.953
You're welcome, by the way.

28:27.331 --> 28:29.375
Oh, my God!

28:29.375 --> 28:31.919
[girl] Yeah!

28:31.919 --> 28:33.712
- Hey.
- Holy shit!

28:33.712 --> 28:36.173
You killed it. You killed it.

28:36.173 --> 28:38.050
[laughs]

28:38.050 --> 28:40.052
I almost puked.

28:40.052 --> 28:42.555
Find a new chew toy, huh?

28:42.555 --> 28:44.140
Heather?

28:45.474 --> 28:46.851
Just be careful.

28:46.851 --> 28:49.311
I hate it when one
of the good ones gets broken.

28:49.311 --> 28:51.313
I'll be gentle.

28:52.773 --> 28:54.650
I don't mean her.

28:55.651 --> 28:57.820
[Williams] "Tom at..."
One, two, three,

28:57.820 --> 29:00.072
- four, five, six,
seven, eight, nine.
- Wait.

29:00.072 --> 29:02.074
No, we're combining this.
This is a 14.

29:02.074 --> 29:04.243
So... "N." "N." "Tom...

29:04.243 --> 29:08.456
Tom at ten."

29:08.456 --> 29:10.166
It's not a scavenger hunt.
It's a start time.

29:10.166 --> 29:11.584
- Whoa, whoa.
- Whatever's happening
tomorrow at 10:00

29:11.584 --> 29:13.043
is happening at the granary
at 10:00.

29:13.043 --> 29:14.503
- Tomorrow.
- Hang on.

29:14.503 --> 29:17.089
- This graffiti
went up yesterday.
- Right.

29:17.089 --> 29:19.091
Well, it's almost 11:00.

29:19.091 --> 29:20.968
Shit. Cortez!

29:20.968 --> 29:22.428
- Gonzalez.
- Oh, shit.

29:22.428 --> 29:24.346
- Chavez.
- [Summer] Up next...

29:24.346 --> 29:26.599
Dodge Mason.

29:26.599 --> 29:29.768
- [cheering]
- Dodge Mason, you're up.

29:38.027 --> 29:40.029
Got to piss.

29:43.782 --> 29:45.409
[boy] You got this!

29:46.785 --> 29:48.621
[girl] Careful!

29:54.418 --> 29:56.921
[Diggins] All right.
And, Dodge Mason,

29:56.921 --> 29:59.507
timer starts in three, two,

29:59.507 --> 30:01.550
- one!
- Go!

30:01.550 --> 30:03.886
[cheering]

30:03.886 --> 30:05.888
[boy] Dodge is a pro!

30:05.888 --> 30:07.515
[boy 2] Go, Dodge!

30:09.517 --> 30:10.935
[grunting]

30:10.935 --> 30:13.854
[gasping and screaming]

30:13.854 --> 30:15.773
- Whoa, whoa, whoa, shit!
- Oh, shit!

30:17.358 --> 30:19.360
[metal creaking]

30:21.862 --> 30:23.113
[Natalie] Oh, my God.

30:41.924 --> 30:43.926
♪ ♪

30:48.556 --> 30:50.558
[cheering in distance]

30:53.769 --> 30:56.772
[whooping and cheering]

30:56.772 --> 30:58.941
- Holy shit.
- [whooping]

30:58.941 --> 31:01.944
[boy] Go! Go!

31:01.944 --> 31:03.529
- [cheering]
- [Diggins] Oh!

31:03.529 --> 31:05.197
Dodge Mason!

31:05.197 --> 31:06.240
Unbelievable!

31:06.240 --> 31:07.950
Un-frigging-believable!

31:07.950 --> 31:10.786
Dodge Mason at 55 seconds!

31:10.786 --> 31:12.621
- [Summer] Fifty-five seconds!
- He's still in the race!

31:12.621 --> 31:13.831
Dodge is still in the game!

31:20.546 --> 31:23.549
[Ray] Wow, thought
we almost lost you there.

31:26.135 --> 31:28.137
[others gasping]

31:30.764 --> 31:33.934
[excited murmuring]

31:33.934 --> 31:35.728
[chuckles]

31:35.728 --> 31:37.396
Not even a kiss good night?

31:39.189 --> 31:40.649
[others exclaiming]

31:40.649 --> 31:42.318
♪ ♪

31:42.318 --> 31:45.696
[shouting]

31:45.696 --> 31:46.780
Get the fuck off me!

31:46.780 --> 31:49.450
[all clamoring]

31:49.450 --> 31:50.784
Hey! Chill!

31:50.784 --> 31:53.120
Are you fucking kidding me
right now?

31:53.120 --> 31:54.997
Oh, my God.

31:54.997 --> 31:57.833
[siren wailing]

31:57.833 --> 32:00.002
- Cops, cops! Go, go, go!
- Run!

32:00.002 --> 32:03.130
Everybody stay
exactly where you are!

32:03.130 --> 32:04.965
On your knees! Hands up!

32:04.965 --> 32:06.258
[all clamoring]

32:06.258 --> 32:08.427
[shouting]

32:08.427 --> 32:10.012
Heather!

32:10.012 --> 32:12.181
[siren wails]

32:12.181 --> 32:14.683
- All right, stay close, okay?
- Yeah.

32:14.683 --> 32:17.186
This way, this way, this way.

32:17.186 --> 32:18.979
[indistinct shouting]

32:20.230 --> 32:22.149
Ah! Ow!

32:25.569 --> 32:27.946
- My ankle. [grunting]
- Come on.

32:30.449 --> 32:31.825
[grunting]

32:31.825 --> 32:34.912
Get the fuck off me, bitch.
I didn't do anything!

32:35.871 --> 32:37.831
Stay down, stay down.
Right hand...

32:37.831 --> 32:39.958
You motherfucker.

32:39.958 --> 32:42.795
[shouting continues]

32:42.795 --> 32:45.798
[groaning, panting]

32:45.798 --> 32:47.925
- Ow. I need to sit down.
- [Heather] Come on.

32:47.925 --> 32:50.010
- [Dodge] Okay.
- Okay, just make it here.

32:50.010 --> 32:51.512
Oh, my God.
[grunts]

32:51.512 --> 32:52.721
- Okay.
- [panting]

32:53.764 --> 32:55.557
- You okay? Yeah?
- Yeah.

32:55.557 --> 32:57.059
Okay, I think
I'm gonna go call Bishop.

32:57.059 --> 32:58.310
- Okay.
- [breathing heavily]

32:58.310 --> 32:59.478
Can I see?

32:59.478 --> 33:01.563
Um... you don't have to.

33:01.563 --> 33:03.190
It's fine.

33:03.190 --> 33:05.109
- I'm sorry.
- You mind?

33:05.109 --> 33:06.944
[Natalie] No. No, go-go for it.

33:06.944 --> 33:08.153
Okay, so, um...

33:08.153 --> 33:11.073
probably ice this
once you get a second.

33:11.073 --> 33:12.282
- Okay?
- Oh.

33:12.282 --> 33:14.451
- Thank you, Doctor.
- Yeah.

33:14.451 --> 33:17.037
- How's that?
- [gasps] Mm.

33:17.037 --> 33:18.997
- It hurts.
- Okay. Can you hold this?

33:18.997 --> 33:19.998
Yes.

33:19.998 --> 33:21.250
Great.

33:24.461 --> 33:25.963
Um...

33:25.963 --> 33:27.339
[chuckles softly]

33:27.339 --> 33:29.383
Oh, don't worry.
I've had my monthly shower.

33:29.383 --> 33:30.384
Oh.

33:30.384 --> 33:31.593
Lucky me.

33:31.593 --> 33:33.429
[Dodge] Yeah. Let me know
if this is too tight.

33:33.429 --> 33:35.180
[Natalie] And what does this do?

33:36.223 --> 33:38.183
Hopefully just restrict...

33:38.183 --> 33:39.351
your movement.

33:39.351 --> 33:41.311
You study first aid?

33:43.188 --> 33:45.607
- Not really.
- [chuckles]

33:45.607 --> 33:47.651
Cinderella,

33:47.651 --> 33:49.153
- your sock.
- [laughs]

33:49.153 --> 33:50.863
Thanks, Prince Charming.

33:50.863 --> 33:52.364
[Dodge] Sorry.

33:52.364 --> 33:54.074
[Natalie] It's okay.

34:00.539 --> 34:03.542
What was up with you and Ray?

34:03.542 --> 34:06.879
Just, um...

34:06.879 --> 34:08.464
Ray just being an asshole.

34:08.464 --> 34:10.632
- Mm. Of course.
- Yeah.

34:12.885 --> 34:14.636
You're not afraid.

34:16.221 --> 34:17.806
[Dodge] Of what, the game?

34:17.806 --> 34:20.017
Of anything.

34:21.059 --> 34:22.936
Everybody's afraid of something.

34:22.936 --> 34:25.022
- Oh, yeah?
- Oh, yeah.

34:25.022 --> 34:27.191
- Well, what about you?
- Hmm.

34:28.233 --> 34:29.693
Can't tell you that.

34:29.693 --> 34:31.278
Oh, it's that scary?

34:32.279 --> 34:33.989
[chuckles softly]

34:35.407 --> 34:36.825
What about you?

34:36.825 --> 34:37.993
What are you scared of?

34:46.210 --> 34:47.461
[inhales]

34:47.461 --> 34:49.713
Not getting out of here.

34:51.548 --> 34:53.425
Right.

34:53.425 --> 34:55.552
It's pretty terrifying.

34:58.430 --> 35:00.098
- Hey.
- [Dodge] Hey.

35:00.098 --> 35:01.517
Um, we're all good.

35:01.517 --> 35:03.185
Bishop's gonna come back for us.

35:03.185 --> 35:04.269
- We're good to go.
- Okay.

35:04.269 --> 35:05.687
- Sweet.
- Great. You good?

35:05.687 --> 35:07.064
Oh. Thanks.

35:07.064 --> 35:09.274
- Yeah.
- I can... I can manage.

35:09.274 --> 35:11.360
You guys, I'm good.
[chuckles softly]

35:11.360 --> 35:13.612
- [Heather] It's fine.
- Oh.

35:18.909 --> 35:20.494
[Williams]
We caught a bunch of kids

35:20.494 --> 35:22.412
we think were playing Panic
last night.

35:22.412 --> 35:24.414
You're too smart
to get mixed up in that,

35:24.414 --> 35:26.250
- yeah?
- [scoffs]

35:26.250 --> 35:28.293
- Come on, Dad.
- I just want
what's best for you.

35:28.293 --> 35:29.711
- You know that, right?
- [sighs] Yeah.

35:29.711 --> 35:31.839
I know you always think
you know what's best...

35:31.839 --> 35:33.799
Yeah, because I am your father.

35:33.799 --> 35:35.384
Oh, by the way,

35:35.384 --> 35:36.802
did you get a chance
to look at those brochures

35:36.802 --> 35:38.178
from the community college?

35:38.178 --> 35:40.305
- They have
acting classes, baby.
- Dad,

35:40.305 --> 35:41.849
- I just graduated.
- Oh.

35:41.849 --> 35:44.309
I get it. You want to work
at the pharmacy forever.

35:44.309 --> 35:45.644
- That's your business.
- Oh-oh, all right. Okay, okay.

35:45.644 --> 35:47.479
I'll... Fine.
I'll take a look.

35:47.479 --> 35:49.481
[chuckles softly]

35:50.482 --> 35:51.650
[door closes]

35:53.569 --> 35:55.571
I love you!

35:55.571 --> 35:57.573
I know that!

35:57.573 --> 35:58.574
[doorbell chimes]

36:01.577 --> 36:03.579
[indistinct chatter]

36:05.247 --> 36:06.915
[Cortez] Williams.

36:06.915 --> 36:08.292
Yeah.

36:11.962 --> 36:13.589
Do me a favor.
Will you pull the tapes

36:13.589 --> 36:15.674
from the speed trap
south of the granary?

36:15.674 --> 36:17.926
I want to get a good look
at the traffic from that night.

36:17.926 --> 36:20.637
That graffiti
didn't graffiti itself, right?

36:20.637 --> 36:22.639
- [chuckles]
- Hey, Sarah Miller's
still here.

36:22.639 --> 36:24.016
Sounds like she's ready to talk.

36:24.016 --> 36:25.434
Who's Sarah Miller?

36:25.434 --> 36:26.768
Remember Caitlyn Miller?

36:26.768 --> 36:28.645
Well, Sarah's her little sister.

36:28.645 --> 36:30.314
She's the only one
we were able to keep in custody,

36:30.314 --> 36:31.440
thanks to Langley.

36:31.440 --> 36:33.025
She nabbed her
with a beer in her hand

36:33.025 --> 36:34.651
and a dime of marijuana
in her front pocket.

36:34.651 --> 36:36.236
I can start off with her
if you want me to.

36:36.236 --> 36:38.989
No, no, no. You put her
in the interrogation room.

36:38.989 --> 36:40.324
I'll handle it.

36:42.117 --> 36:44.494
Hyenas, John.

36:44.494 --> 36:46.079
These kids, they, uh...

36:46.079 --> 36:47.789
they protect each other,
like hyenas,

36:47.789 --> 36:50.292
until you isolate one of them.
And then, well...

36:50.292 --> 36:52.920
then they just protect
themselves.

36:52.920 --> 36:54.755
Mm.

36:55.797 --> 36:57.799
♪ ♪

37:16.526 --> 37:19.112
♪ ♪

37:30.207 --> 37:31.208
[door opens]

37:31.208 --> 37:33.210
[Cortez] Melanie.

37:33.210 --> 37:35.128
Mel... [sighs]

37:35.128 --> 37:36.880
Melanie.

37:49.393 --> 37:52.062
Caramel?

37:52.062 --> 37:54.189
We talked about this.

37:55.273 --> 37:57.109
I'm sorry.

38:04.324 --> 38:08.078
[sighs] You got to stop
doing this to yourself.

38:10.956 --> 38:12.708
[grunts]

38:14.501 --> 38:17.337
You got to stop
doing this to us.

38:20.549 --> 38:22.801
Melanie.

38:22.801 --> 38:24.219
Mel.

38:34.896 --> 38:36.314
Hey.

38:36.314 --> 38:38.316
You got to stop.

38:38.316 --> 38:40.986
Have you eaten anything all day?

38:42.070 --> 38:43.572
Come here.

38:43.572 --> 38:46.074
Why don't you shower up

38:46.074 --> 38:48.368
and you get your hair all pretty

38:48.368 --> 38:49.536
and we'll go to the Old House

38:49.536 --> 38:50.704
and I'll get you
a double cheeseburger

38:50.704 --> 38:52.622
and those curly fries you love.

38:52.622 --> 38:54.332
Hmm?

38:54.332 --> 38:55.584
Come on.

38:55.584 --> 38:57.210
Let me get this.

38:57.210 --> 39:00.047
I think it'll be good
for you to get out of the house.

39:00.047 --> 39:01.548
Do you?

39:02.549 --> 39:04.134
[sighs]

39:06.261 --> 39:07.512
[clicks tongue]

39:08.513 --> 39:09.931
Fine.

39:15.771 --> 39:17.272
[Melanie groans softly]

39:18.857 --> 39:21.068
You all right?

39:38.460 --> 39:40.462
♪ ♪

39:51.348 --> 39:53.183
[Cortez] One thing
is being good at barbecue.

39:53.183 --> 39:55.185
Another thing is being
a pitmaster.

39:55.185 --> 39:57.312
It's all in the wrist.
You want to flip it up and...

39:57.312 --> 39:59.439
- [Jimmy] Uh, okay. Okay.
- Oh! [laughs]

39:59.439 --> 40:00.857
- [Jimmy laughs]
- [Cortez] Saw that.

40:00.857 --> 40:02.192
I want to say happy birthday

40:02.192 --> 40:03.693
- to the most...
- [Melanie] To the most...

40:03.693 --> 40:06.279
- beautiful woman... Girl.
- [Cortez] Girl. Girl.

40:06.279 --> 40:08.490
- Mwah. In Texas.
- In Texas,

40:08.490 --> 40:10.117
- who gets...
- The great state of Texas.

40:10.117 --> 40:12.160
- ...prettier every year.
- And prettier.

40:12.160 --> 40:13.662
- Announcing the world-famous
macaroni salad.
- [Cortez] I love you, baby.

40:13.662 --> 40:15.872
- [Melanie] I love you, too.
- [Jimmy] Oh, there she is.

40:15.872 --> 40:17.874
- By yours truly.
What are you doing?
- There's Abby.

40:17.874 --> 40:19.459
You're a little rascal,
aren't you?

40:19.459 --> 40:21.670
- Come on!
- [laughter]

40:21.670 --> 40:23.296
Come on. Get in there.

40:23.296 --> 40:25.048
- Take a picture.
- This is good.
- Come on, son.

40:25.048 --> 40:27.259
- [Abby] Smile for the camera.
- Okay.

40:27.259 --> 40:29.553
- [Abby] Smile, Jimmy.
- Wait, wait, wait, wait,
wait, wait, wait. All right.

40:29.553 --> 40:31.763
[Jimmy] Getting a little bald
up there, man.

40:31.763 --> 40:33.932
- [Abby] Oh!
- [Jimmy] What's up?

40:33.932 --> 40:35.392
[Abby] All right,
show me the teeth.

40:35.392 --> 40:37.477
Not like a raccoon, Jimmy.
Smile.

40:37.477 --> 40:39.563
- Aw.
- Happy birthday, baby.

40:39.563 --> 40:41.106
- Happy birthday, Mom.
- We love you.

40:41.106 --> 40:43.108
[overlapping chatter]

40:43.108 --> 40:44.943
[Cortez] Give me
those hot dog buns. Let's go.

40:44.943 --> 40:47.529
[Jimmy] Go long, Dad.
Go long!

40:47.529 --> 40:49.531
- Old man's still got it!
- [Cortez] Old man?

40:49.531 --> 40:52.534
[♪ Midlake: "Acts of Man"]

